The paper deals with visual recognition tasks such as multimedia event detection and recognition, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) communities. The proposed method involves object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision and machine learning (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the use of statistics and pooling techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) subfields.
